Building and installing openModeller
====================================

1. Install proj4 library (www.remotesensing.org/proj).
   Note that openModeller was tested with version 4.4.7


2. Install the latest GDAL version. At this moment the stable version
   is 1.1.9 but it is better get the latest source from CVS:

   % export CVSROOT=:pserver:anonymous@cvs.remotesensing.org:/cvsroot
   % cvs login
   Password: anonymous
   % cvs checkout gdal


4. Follow this procedure:

   a) Unpack openModeller:

      $ tar xvzf openmodeller*

   b) Change to the openModeller directory:

      $ cd openmodeller*

   c) Configure openModeller for your particular system:

      $ ./configure

   d) Build openModeller:

      $ make

   e) Install openModeller in your system (you need root privileges).

      $ su -c 'make install'

   If you do not have root privileges or if you want to install openModeller
   in another path than "/usr", i.e. in a non standard place, you can do:

   $ tar xvzf openmodeller*
   $ cd openmodeller*
   $ ./configure --prefix=<OMPATH>
   $ make
   $ make install

   Where <OMPATH> represents the directory path to install openModeller.


5. In the default installation <OMPATH>=/usr. The following files are installed:

   # Binaries
   <OMPATH>/bin/om_console           # A simple openModeller console client
   <OMPATH>/bin/om_viewer            # A simple X11 modeller viewer.

   # Libraries
   <OMPATH>/lib/libopenmodeller.so   # openModeller dynamic shared library.
   <OMPATH>/lib/libopenmodeller.a    # openModeller static library.
   <OMPATH>/lib/libopenmodeller.la
   <OMPATH>/lib/libopenmodeller.so.0
   <OMPATH>/lib/libopenmodeller.so.0.0.0

   # C++ headers
   <OMPATH>/include/om_algorithm.hh
   <OMPATH>/include/om_algorithm_metadata.hh
   <OMPATH>/include/om_control.hh
   <OMPATH>/include/om_defs.hh
   <OMPATH>/include/om.hh
   <OMPATH>/include/om_log.hh
   <OMPATH>/include/om_occurrences.hh
   <OMPATH>/include/om_sampled_data.hh
   <OMPATH>/include/om_sampler.hh

   # Modelling algorithms plugins
   <OMPATH>/lib/openmodeller/*


8. To run om_console go to directory "examples" and get at least one
   map file to do a simple test: 
    $ cd examples
    $ wget http://openmodeller.cria.org.br/download/rain_coolest.tgz
    $ tar xvzf rain_coolest.tgz


9. Read the request.txt file. It tells openModeller what to do.


10. Run openModeller console version:
    $ om_console request.txt

    The output will be in furcata.tif.

    Obs: be sure that "<PATH_TO_INSTALL>/bin" is in your PATH!


11. If you have a system with X11 you can:

    Visualize the maps with:
    $ om_viewer request.txt

    Visualize the resulted model with:
    $ om_viewer -r request.txt



